pre.code:
library OpioidCDS_STU3_REC_08 version '0.1.0'
using FHIR version '3.0.0'
include FHIRHelpers version '3.0.0' called FHIRHelpers include OpioidCDS_STU3_Common version '0.1.0' called Common
/* ** ** Recommendation #8 ** Incorporate into the management plan strategies to mitigate risk; ** including considering offering naloxone when factors that increase risk for opioid overdose are present ** */
/* Trigger context: Primary care/ambulatory care Trigger event: Prescription of opioid with ambulatory care abuse potential Assumptions: Count only ambulatory prescriptions Inclusion criteria (OR): Average MME >= 50 On benzodiazepine History of alcohol abuse or drug abuse (in FHIR Condition, which means problem list at this point for many EHRs. Univ. of Utah has created separate interfaces for pulling in past medical history and encounter diagnosis, but this will not be widely available) Exclusion criterion: On naloxone Notification: Consider offering naloxone given following risk factor(s) for opioid overdose: (average MME >= 50/day), (concurrent use of benzodiazepine), (history of alcohol or drug abuse). Ref: CDC Recommendation #8. Value sets: Custom value set for relevant substance abuse (Rob will create) This needs to include ICD9 and/or 10 For now, defining value sets as descendants of: ICD10: F10-F19, Mental and behavioral disorders due to psychoactive substance use ICD9: 304, Drug dependence and 303, Alcohol dependence syndrome
Plan Definition: http://build.fhir.org/ig/cqframework/opioid-cds/PlanDefinition-opioidcds-08.html */
parameter ContextPrescriptions List<MedicationRequest>
context Patient
define "Validate Trigger Event": exists( ContextPrescriptions triggerScript where triggerScript.medication in Common."Ambulatory Abuse Potential Opioids" )
define "Inclusion Criteria": AgeInYears() >= 18 and "Validate Trigger Event" and not "Exclusion Criteria" and ( "Total MME" >= 50 'mg/d' or "On Benzodiazepine" or "Has Substance Abuse History" )
define "Exclusion Criteria": "On Naloxone" or Common."End of Life Assessment" or Common."Is Context Prescription End of Life Opioid?"(ContextPrescriptions)
define "Total MME": Common.TotalMME(Common."Active Ambulatory Opioid Rx" union ContextPrescriptions)
define "On Naloxone": exists( Common."Active Ambulatory Naloxone Rx" )
define "On Benzodiazepine": exists( Common."Active Ambulatory Benzodiazepine Rx" )
define "Has Substance Abuse History": exists ( [Condition: Common."Substance Abuse"] )
define "Get Indicator": if "Inclusion Criteria" then 'warning' else null
define "Get Summary": if "Inclusion Criteria" then 'Incorporate into the management plan strategies to mitigate risk; including considering offering naloxone when factors that increase risk for opioid overdose are present' else null
define "Detail Descriptions": { { hasCondition: "Total MME" >= 50 'mg/day', text: 'Average MME (' + ToString("Total MME") + ') >= 50 mg/day' }, { hasCondition: "On Benzodiazepine", text: 'concurrent use of benzodiazepine'}, { hasCondition: "Has Substance Abuse History", text: 'history of alcohol or drug abuse' } }
define "Detail List": Combine("Detail Descriptions" dd where dd.hasCondition return dd.text, ', ')
define "Get Detail": if "Inclusion Criteria" then 'Consider offering naloxone given following risk factor(s) for opioid overdose: ' + if "Detail List" is not null and "Detail List" != '' then "Detail List" + '.' else 'N/A.' else null
